The paper deals with two-player games of infinite duration, which are a topic of interest in game theory (cs.GT) and logic (cs.LO). The discussion of deterministic winning strategies suggests a focus on algorithms and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of equivalence relations and the consideration of games with states and colors suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
